    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-07-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="626" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Sullivan</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-07-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 5, 1867.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> A dispatch of the 14th of June has been
                            received from Mr. Rice, in which he refers to the question of
                            extraordinary taxation by the State of Panama, for purposes connected
                            with the civil war in Colombia. The character of that war and the
                            situation of the beligerents still remain very obscure, so far as
                            information has reached this government.</p>
                <p>I have, therefore, to refer you to my circular dispatch of the 13th of
                            June, and to inform you that at present the views therein expressed have
                            undergone no change.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peter</hi> J. <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.,
                                    &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>(Same to F. W. Rice, esq., United States Consul at Aspinwall.)</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
